        "content": "<p>Suppose a proposition depending on a variable <code>t</code> has two instance of <code>Decidable</code> defined for it, but one of them depends on the typeclass <code>[MyClass t]</code> being availiable - it's more efficient, so essentially if it IS possible to use this instance for deciding the proposition, that is preferred. Will Lean automatically use the more-specific instance if it is available? Is there a way to make sure it does?</p>",
        "id": 544193773,
        "sender_full_name": "Wrenna Robson",
        "timestamp": 1760109305
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>instance (priority := 100)</code></p>",
        "id": 544194130,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1760109396
